# Stevens Cup Cyclocross App - Project Rules

## Context
This is a cyclocross competition rankings app using Next.js 15, TypeScript, Drizzle ORM, and Neon database. The design is mobile-first for race staff use.

## Key Entities
The app follows this hierarchy: Series → Events → Contests → Races

## Technology Stack
- Next.js 15
- TypeScript
- Drizzle ORM
- Neon database
- Mobile-first design

## Development Guidelines
- Focus on mobile-first design for race staff
- Follow the entity hierarchy: Series → Events → Contests → Races
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Leverage Drizzle ORM for database operations
- Ensure responsive design for mobile devices 

## Documentation
Documentation follows the idea of ADR (architecture design record). For every major change to the project there is a numbered and dated document in `docs/adr`. There is no formal review or ADR status now.
 - when working with Cursor prompt, next document can hold the summary of the prompt(s) and solution
 - document should be concise, it is intended to be read in the future to unterstand the development path 